"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643185","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-01","<p>Ofgem’s regulations state that energy suppliers must provide information on any alternative cheaper tariffs that they offer, on the front page of every customers’ energy bills and annual statements and on notification of increase in charges.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-12-01T17:08:10.62Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643185/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643185/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many times per year and in what format customers of (a) British Gas, (b) EDF, (c) EON, (d) nPower, (e) Scottish Power and (f) SSE who are on standard variable tariffs receive Supplier Cheapest Tariff information.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","54590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643186","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-01","<p>Energy suppliers must include on bills and other communications to domestic customers information about the savings they can make by moving to their supplier’s cheapest tariff.</p><p> </p><p>Suppliers are not required to provide any additional written communications to recipients of the Warm Home Discount scheme concerning switching to the lower tariff, and Ofgem does not monitor suppliers’ tariff communications with scheme recipients.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-12-01T17:05:11.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643186/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643186/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Warm Home Discount Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what additional written communications each of the Big Six energy companies give to recipients of the Warm Home Discount to support them in switching to the lowest priced energy tariffs; and whether the provision of such communication is monitored by Ofgem.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","54589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643187","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-01","<p>The Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) does not collect or hold data on those who receive Cold Weather Payments. BEIS collects data from energy suppliers regarding the tariff that customers are on as part of the Domestic Fuel Inquiry. The tariff data is collected from the energy suppliers in confidence; As such we cannot provide figures for specific companies. In quarter 2 2016, 69 per cent of domestic standard electricity customers were on a variable tariff. For domestic gas customers, 67 per cent were on a variable tariff. This data is published as part of our Quarterly Energy Prices publication which can be found in tables 2.4.2 and 2.5.2 (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/annual-domestic-energy-price-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/annual-domestic-energy-price-statistics</a> ).</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-12-01T17:06:49.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643187/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643187/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643187/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Cold Weather Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of Cold Weather Payment recipients whose energy is supplied by (a) British Gas, (b) EDF, (c) EON, (d) nPower, (e) Scottish Power, (f) SSE and (g) all Big Six companies are on their supplier's standard variable tariff.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","54591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643188","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-01","<p>Department for Business, Energy and Industry Strategy Ministers have met with a number of energy supply companies to discuss a wide range of issues.</p><p> </p><p>Consumers without access to the internet can shop around to find a better deal for their energy by using any price comparison company which is accredited to the Confidence Code administered by Ofgem and provides a free telephone price comparison service. In addition Citizen Advice offers advice and support on energy switching.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has made it clear that it wants to see companies treating all of their customers fairly – not just those who switch.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-12-01T17:10:22.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643188/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643188/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643188/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will discuss with energy companies the potential exclusion of customers who cannot access IT services from cheaper tariffs.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","54586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643189","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-28","<p>The number of applications approved for accreditation under the renewables obligation (RO) for onshore and offshore wind projects in the UK between the financial years 2010/11 to 2015/16 were:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Technology </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total number of applications for accreditation between 2010/11 and 2015/16</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Micro onshore wind projects up to and including 50kW capacity</p></td><td><p>142</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Onshore wind projects above 50kW capacity</p></td><td><p>590</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Offshore wind projects</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Ofgem:</p><p>RO accredited stations list (downloaded 24 November 2016): <a href="https://www.renewablesandchp.ofgem.gov.uk/Public/ReportManager.aspx?ReportVisibility=1&amp;ReportCategory=0" target="_blank">https://www.renewablesandchp.ofgem.gov.uk/Public/ReportManager.aspx?ReportVisibility=1&amp;ReportCategory=0</a></p><p>The costs of the RO are reclaimed from electricity consumers, not from general taxation. The annual costs of supporting onshore and offshore wind through the RO from 2010/11 to 2015/16, in £ million nominal prices were:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>RO costs £/million </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Onshore wind</p></td><td><p>£397.8</p></td><td><p>£482.6</p></td><td><p>£557.1</p></td><td><p>£755.6</p></td><td><p>£786.8</p></td><td><p>£803.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Offshore wind</p></td><td><p>£253.9</p></td><td><p>£371.1</p></td><td><p>£698.5</p></td><td><p>£988.7</p></td><td><p>£1,108.0</p></td><td><p>£1,429.7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: Ofgem:</p><p>Renewables Obligation library: <a href="https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/environmental-programmes/ro/contacts-publications-and-data/publications-library-renewables-obligation-ro" target="_blank">https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/environmental-programmes/ro/contacts-publications-and-data/publications-library-renewables-obligation-ro</a></p><p>Renewables Obligation Annual Report 2014-15: <a href="https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/publications-and-updates/renewables-obligation-ro-annual-report-2014-15" target="_blank">https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/publications-and-updates/renewables-obligation-ro-annual-report-2014-15</a></p><p>Renewables Obligation register and compliance certificates report: <a href="https://www.renewablesandchp.ofgem.gov.uk/Public/ReportManager.aspx?ReportVisibility=1&amp;ReportCategory=0" target="_blank">https://www.renewablesandchp.ofgem.gov.uk/Public/ReportManager.aspx?ReportVisibility=1&amp;ReportCategory=0</a></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-28T14:52:58.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643189/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643189/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643189/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Wind Power: Renewables Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many applications were made under the renewables obligation for (a) onshore and (b) offshore wind; and what the annual cost to the public purse was of each of those subsidies between 2010 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","54504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643190","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-29","<p>The following tables show the number of total applications for air source heat pumps and ground source heat pumps under the domestic Renewable Heat Incentive. The latest application data the department has is up to the end of October 2016; as such 2016 does not represent a full year of applications.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Air source heat pumps</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total applications (new and legacy)</p></td><td><p>7,689</p></td><td><p>13,714</p></td><td><p>4,783</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Actuals and Accruals</p></td><td><p>£1,873,300</p></td><td><p>£11,027,489</p></td><td><p>£13,317,544</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Ground source heat pumps</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total applications (new and legacy)</p></td><td><p>3,127</p></td><td><p>3,727</p></td><td><p>1,131</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Actuals and Accruals</p></td><td><p>£3,073,978</p></td><td><p>£16,554,779</p></td><td><p>£19,054,131</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-29T14:17:34.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643190/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643190/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many new applications have been made to the domestic Renewable Heat Incentive scheme since it opened in April 2014 for (a) air-source and (b) ground and water-source heat pumps; and what the annual cost to the public purse was of each of those subsidies.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","54505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643191","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-29","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy does not hold information on the length of time that a customer has been on the same tariff.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-11-29T15:33:26.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643191/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643191/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the (a) mode and (b) mean length of time is that Big Six energy customers stay on their supplier's standard variable tariff.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","54535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643192","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-01","<p>The Government wants to see energy companies treating all of their customers fairly, including those on Standard Variable tariffs, not just those who switch.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) collects data, including customers’ tariff information, from energy companies as part of the domestic fuels inquiry (DFI). In the second quarter of 2016, 69 per cent of domestic standard electricity customers and 67 per cent of domestic gas customers were on variable tariffs. This data is published within our Quarterly Energy Prices publication and can be found in Tables 2.4.2 and 2.5.2 which is available online: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/annual-domestic-energy-price-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/annual-domestic-energy-price-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p>BEIS started collecting this data at the end of 2012; therefore annual data is available for 2013 onwards. These figures are based on the DFI which covers around 85 per cent of the market. This includes all of the big 6 energy suppliers, Northern Ireland suppliers and one smaller supplier. The proportion of customers on variable tariffs, including standard variable tariffs, is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Standard Electricity</p></td><td><p>Gas</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>81</p></td><td><p>79</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>75</p></td><td><p>73</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>73</p></td><td><p>70</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-12-01T17:22:22.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643192/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643192/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of customers of the Big Six energy companies have been on their supplier's standard variable tariff for each year from 2006 to 2016.","false","Biography information for Glyn Davies","Montgomeryshire","Glyn Davies","54536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643194","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-28","<p>Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy ministers and officials meet Department for Culture, Media and Sport colleagues to discuss issues in the telecommunications sector as required. In line with the practice of successive administrations, details of ministerial discussions are not routinely disclosed.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-28T14:54:45.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643194/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643194/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643194/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Telecommunications: Competition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, on what dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department met with their counterparts in the Department for Culture, Media and Sport to discuss competition in the telecommunications sector in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","54416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643195","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-28","<p>Ministers and officials meet regularly with small businesses to discuss a variety of topics.</p><p>All Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly on the Gov.uk website at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-quarterly-publications-april-to-june-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-quarterly-publications-april-to-june-2012</a></p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-28T14:53:47.14Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643195/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643195/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, on what dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department met small businesses to discuss company law reform in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","54417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643196","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-28","<p>The Department does not currently hold information on the effect of limited companies operating under umbrella companies on official statistics on independent entrepreneurship.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-11-28T14:55:33.483Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643196/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643196/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-23","Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of limited companies operating under umbrella companies on official statistics on independent entrepreneurship.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","54454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643197","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-28","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) created the Employment Status and Intermediaries Team to focus on employment status and employment intermediary risks. HMRC’s risk-based approach to compliance, the outcome of Employment Tribunal cases, third-party data and other data will help inform the Government’s assessment of the number of people whose employment status has been incorrectly classified.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-28T14:17:52.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643197/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643197/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-23","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps the Government is taking to assess the number of people working for (a) a single employer and (b) an online platform who are incorrectly classified as (i) independent contractors, (ii) self-employed and (iii) independent limited companies.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","54441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643198","Department for Education","false","2016-11-28","<p>Part-time students starting a second degree course in any Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths (STEM) subject will be eligible for student support from the 2017/18 academic year. We expect that that these changes will reduce barriers to people studying and help fill the high-level skills gaps that hold back parts of the economy.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-11-28T16:53:12.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643198/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643198/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-23","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the potential merits of introducing loans for second degrees to help people in and out of work to meet current and future high skills level gaps in England.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","54453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643199","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-28","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs has not estimated how many contractors, constituted as independent limited companies, are working under the control and management of umbrella companies.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-28T14:17:26.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643199/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643199/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-23","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his most recent estimate is of the number of contractors working under the control and management of umbrella companies that are constituted as independent limited companies.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","54442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643200","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>The Department for International Trade collects and validates information on known foreign direct investment (FDI) projects that materialise in the UK during a financial year. The results are published annually to allow for full quality control of the results, and can be found on Gov.uk.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T17:21:04.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643200/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643200/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many inward investment projects have been confirmed by his Department in the first half of the 2016-17 tax year.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643201","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>Records of Cabinet meetings or those of its sub-committees are confidential.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T16:59:58.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643201/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643201/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643201/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","World Trade Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will make available the analysis presented to the Cabinet sub-committee on Europe at the meeting of 18 October 2016 on the consequences for the UK economy of adopting World Trade Organisation rules.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643202","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>The UK is already a founding member of the World Trade Organisation (WTO). The process of separating our position from that of the EU within the WTO is distinct from the Article 50 process.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T16:40:43.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643202/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643202/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643202/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","World Trade Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, when he expects the UK will be in a position to confirm its status at the World Trade Organisation after the conclusion of the Article 50 process.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643203","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-29","<p>I refer to the hon Member to the answer I gave him on the 28th of November, UIN 54495.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-29T14:03:44.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643203/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643203/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643203/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether he has made an assessment of the adequacy of the number of staff in his Department who have responsibility for processing freedom of information requests.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643204","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-28","<p>Adequate arrangements for processing Freedom of Information requests in the Department have been in place since its formation.</p><p>Figures on the number and timeliness of response to FOI requests received at the Department for International Trade are being collected and will be published as part of the National Statistics FOI Bulletin on the 15th of December.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-28T16:42:25.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643204/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643204/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643204/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, for what reasons his Department has not responded to all of its Freedom of Information requests within the statutory time limit.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643205","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-28","<p>This Department does not hold centrally the information you request and it could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-28T17:21:20.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643205/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643205/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643205/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will provide a list of the representatives from external organisations that officials of his Department have met since the creation of his Department.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643206","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-28","<p>Details of Ministerial meetings, are published quarterly on gov.uk at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=ministerial+meetings&amp;publication_filter_option=transparency-data&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=all&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-28T17:06:24.58Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643206/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643206/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will provide a list of the representatives from external organisations that Ministers of his Department have met since the creation of his Department.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643207","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-29","<p>The Prime Minister has established the Department for International Trade to promote British trade across the world, and the Department’s ministers will provide further information on its strategy and policies over the coming months.</p><p>The UK continues to be a global leader on climate action, as demonstrated by our recent ratification of the Paris Agreement and agreement of the UK’s Fifth Carbon Budget in July. The UK has long supported the promotion of our values globally and this will continue as we leave the EU. While we remain members of the EU, the UK will participate constructively in EU decision making on trade issues, including on environmental provisions within trade agreements.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-29T14:51:51.693Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643207/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643207/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643207/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643207/answer/previousversion/23091","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps he plans to take to ensure that all future trade and investment deals are consistent with the UK's international obligations to tackle climate change.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643208","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>It would not be appropriate to give the names of individual firms.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T17:39:39.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643208/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643208/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643208/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Legal Opinion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 12 September 2016 to Question 44715, which legal firms have offered his Department pro bono support.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643209","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>The analysts and lawyers referred to are internal.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T16:38:26.49Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643209/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643209/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643209/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Legal Opinion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 48262, which external firms will be providing the (a) analysts and (b) lawyers referred to in that Answer.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643210","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>Two per cent of the UK’s exports of goods and services and four per cent of the UK’s imports of goods and services in 2015 went to or came from European Economic Area countries and non-EU members of the Customs Union.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T16:42:21.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643210/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643210/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643210/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 14 October 2016 to Question 46441, what estimate he has made of the total annual value to the UK of exports and imports related to preferential access to EEA countries and non-EU members of the Customs Union.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","54508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643211","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-01","<p>The Prime Minister has instructed all departments to identify potential opportunities that will arise from exiting the European Union.</p><p>This Government is united in its ambition to deliver a successful withdrawal from the European Union and a new relationship with Europe, and departments will work together to deliver this.</p><p>In the Department for International Trade our responsibilities include:</p><p> </p><ul><li>Promoting and supporting UK exports of goods and services, including through export finance and insurance to support a growing economy that works for everyone;</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Maximising opportunities for wealth creation through supporting Foreign Direct Investment and Outward Direct Investment;</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Delivering the best international trading framework for the UK to maximise trade and investment opportunities.</li></ul><p> </p><p>In all of these areas there may be opportunities that relate to the UK’s exit from the European Union. We are working with the Department for Exiting the European Union to seize these opportunities, and ensure a smooth process of exit on the best possible terms for the United Kingdom and its citizens.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-01T16:37:29.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643211/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643211/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643211/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many projects in operation in his Department are related to the UK's exit of the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","54529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643212","Department for International Trade","false","2016-11-29","<p>The UK Permanent Representative to the World Trade Organisation (WTO) engages with a range of partners on trade issues, including the WTO Secretariat and other WTO members. In leaving the EU our goal will be to minimise disruption to our trading relationships with other WTO members.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-11-29T14:51:21.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643212/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643212/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/643212/answer/previousversion/23164","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-11-23","World Trade Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what discussions the UK representative at the World Trade Organisation has had on future arrangements which may be necessary when the UK leaves the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","54653"
